{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 2:2Figure 2: A comparative analysis of TinyLLM against the state-of-the-art Distill-step-by-step method using 80M and 250M FLAN-T5 model architectures across various training set sizes.",
    "Dotted line indicates the full fine-tuning (FF) using 100% dataset.",
    "It is evident that TinyLLM consistently surpasses the performance of both Distill-step-by-step and full fine-tuning.",
    "Notably, TinyLLM achieves this superior accuracy while employing substantially fewer training examples.",
    "removes the use of in-context examples during rationale generation."
  ]
}